                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14136365" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2014 22:19:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I added more fix versions because this seems generally useful. I can put up patches for branches other than master, no problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14136405" author="stack" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2014 22:43:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In the past, I worked at a shop that had thousands of tables.  We added an &apos;owner&apos; attribute (&apos;table creator&apos; is probably better, less committment), just so we could figure who to chase if table was acting up or if it seemed dead.  Owner is gone now?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Seems like a good idea to me. Let me add the ops label.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14136453" author="eclark" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2014 23:08:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can we make it multiple field?&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;d really want to have something like owner, email, and webpage.  Though I bet others would want something different.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14136465" author="mbertozzi" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2014 23:11:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eclark&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eclark&quot;&gt;Elliott Clark&lt;/a&gt; I was thinking at something enforced on the server side via getCurrentUser(). do you want something like the old owner configurable via create/alter?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14136494" author="eclark" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2014 23:30:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I was thinking more along with.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14136598" author="ghelmling" created="Wed, 17 Sep 2014 01:00:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems like the current support for HTD metadata (&quot;values&quot;) could handle this.  Just need to initialize a metadata value for &quot;owner&quot; with getCurrentUser() upon table creation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it needs to be editable (which the metadata is of course), since people can leave the organization, move teams, etc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14136609" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 17 Sep 2014 01:07:28 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Just need to initialize a metadata value for &quot;owner&quot; with getCurrentUser() upon table creation.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We almost already have this, and deprecated...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;HTableDescriptor:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
  @Deprecated
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void setOwner(User owner) {
    setOwnerString(owner != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; ? owner.getShortName() : &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;);
  }

  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// used by admin.rb:alter(table_name,*args) to update owner.
&lt;/span&gt;  @Deprecated
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void setOwnerString(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; ownerString) {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ownerString != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;) {
      setValue(OWNER_KEY, ownerString);
    } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
      remove(OWNER_KEY);
    }
  }

  @Deprecated
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; getOwnerString() {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (getValue(OWNER_KEY) != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;) {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; Bytes.toString(getValue(OWNER_KEY));
    }
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Note that every table should have an owner (i.e. should have OWNER_KEY set).
&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// hbase:meta and -ROOT- should &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; system user as owner, not &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; (see
&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// MasterFileSystem.java:bootstrap()).
&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;;
  }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Right now only the AccessController will set OWNER_KEY on the HTD if it is active when the table is created.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14233788" author="apurtell" created="Thu, 4 Dec 2014 01:38:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No patch or progress for a while, unscheduling from releases until we have one&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
